Snickerdoodle Cheesecake Bars
  --Philadelphia (KraftHeintz) 

1 1/2 c flour
3/4 c + 2 tsp sugar, divided
1 tbsp + 1/8 tsp cinnamon, divided
3/4 c cold butter, cut up
2x8 oz pkg cream cheese, softened
1 tbsp vanilla
1/4 c sour cream
2 eggs

Heat oven to 325F. Line 8x8" baking dish with foil, making a sling. Combine flour, 1/4 c sugar, and 1 tbsp cinnamon in medium bowl. Cut in the butter until mixture resembles coars crumbs. Reserve 1/2 c of the mixture for later use; press remaining onto bottom and 1/2" up the sides of prepared dish. Bake 25 min, or until lightly browned. Beat cream cheese, vanilla, and 1/2 c of remaining sugar in large bowl with mixer until blended. Add sour cream; mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing on low speed after each until just blended. Set aside. Combine remaining sugar and cinnamon. Pour cream cheese mixture into crust; top with reserved crumb and cinnamon sugar. Bake 45-50 min or until center is almost set; cool completely. Refrigerate for 4hrs before removing from dish and cutting into bars.


